line_1: And might, perhaps, have well essay'd
line_2: My Youth met Fortune fair array'd,

line_1: The Youth to chear the drooping Dame essay'd,
line_2: When straight a Boar came rushing thro' the Shade;

line_1: To pierce his trembling Heart he thrice essay'd,
line_2: And thrice his coward Arm deny'd its Aid:

line_1: WHEN I, in feeble Verse, essay'd
line_2: A Lyric Muse flew o'er my Head,

line_1: To yield a fresh and friendly Bud essay'd,
line_2: And if some naked Stalk, not quite decay'd,

line_1: Thus the fond swain on dorick oate essay'd,
line_2: Trembling he strove to court the tuneful maid

line_1: Thus the fond swain on dorick oate essay'd,
line_2: Unseen, unheard, beneath an hawthorn shade.
And many a weary moment stay'd;

line_1: Perdie, quoth he, my fortune be essay'd,
line_2: The nymphs he met, for much he was affraid

line_1: Perdie, quoth he, my fortune be essay'd,
line_2: At flatt'ry's tongue full oft will virtue fade;

line_1: Perdie, quoth he, my fortune be essay'd,
line_2: What shall he do? to win his lovely maid
Call'd the deep Mystic to my Aid:

line_1: My ardent love in vain essay'd,
line_2: But still a thousand pranks she play'd;

line_1: Vain Man! since first thy blushing Sire essay'd
line_2: His Folly with connected Leaves to shade;
Let Hymen sooth the bashfull maid,
